    substitution:'Russia IS the substitute. Constraint is logistics/sanctions, not Hormuz.',
    hormuz:'Maximum upside — Brent could replicate 1990\'s doubling. Urals discount compresses. Wheat/fertilizer co-spike.',
    strike:'Moderate-to-large upside via Brent premium.',
    cable:'Largely insulated; indirect benefit from rival-hub disruption.',
    ceasefire:'Only loser case — premium unwinds, Brent falls, squeezing budget. Ceasefire is Russia\'s worst scenario.',
    history:'Every Gulf shock is a Russian windfall. 1973/1979: USSR beneficiary. 2022: $230B surplus, gas revenue doubled to $130B.',
    secondOrder:'Fertilizer market share surge — with Hormuz disrupting ~50% of global urea/sulfur, Russian fertilizers become the only uncontested alternative. Gives Moscow leverage over India, Egypt, Brazil that reduces sanctions\' political cost.',
    confidence:'high',
  },
  {
    id:'south-korea', title:'South Korea', gdp:'$1.7T', tag:'loser', tagColor:'#ef4444',
    summary:'~100% crude imported, ~70% via Hormuz, ~19.5% LNG exposed. $150/bbl = +2.9pp inflation, -0.8pp growth. KOSPI crashed 12% on March 4. Silver lining: 66% of global LNG-carrier orderbook ($71.3B).',
    energy:'~100% crude imported; ~70% via Hormuz. ~19.5% LNG exposed. Power: coal+gas ~58%, nuclear ~31%.',
    food:'Net importer but not Gulf-sourced. Lower-tier vulnerability.',
    trade:'Petrochemicals -15.5%. Samsung+SK Hynix 75% global DRAM. Shipbuilding 22% global share, 66% of LNG-carrier orderbook ($71.3B).',
    financial:'$100/bbl: +1.1pp inflation, -0.3pp growth. $150/bbl: +2.9pp, -0.8pp. 5 trillion won supplementary budget (April).',
    substitution:'Australia LNG (31.4%) and US LNG diversify. Nuclear (31%) is non-import buffer. Crude hard to substitute short-term.',
    hormuz:'~70% crude + ~19.5% LNG at risk. KOSPI -12%. Stagflation risk. Shipbuilding demand surge partially offsets.',
    strike:'$100/bbl: +1.1pp inflation; petrochemical margins squeezed.',
    cable:'Indirect — financial/trading latency; global risk-off.',
    ceasefire:'Relief rally — won recovers, import bill falls; shipbuilding orders may soften as scarcity premium fades.',
